<p>After suffering through yet more broadband problems with John&#8217;s cable modem, Dave and John get a Geek Gab out, albeit a day late. Dave&#8217;s chiming in from Austin, Texas, and he and John talk about their favorite ways to keep their Macs running smooth, and how to tell when it&#8217;s not! John also wraps up his Apple tech support experience for us all, as well.</p>
<p><strong>Show notes for TMO To Go: Mac Geek Gab For August 22th, 2005</strong></p>
<p>Podcast Link: <a href="http://mp3.macobserver.com/podcast/mgg12.mp3" data-wpel-link="external" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer">TMO To Go: Mac Geek Gab, August 22th, 2005</a></p>
<p>After suffering through yet more broadband problems with John&#8217;s cable modem, Dave and John get a Geek Gab out, albeit a day late. Dave&#8217;s chiming in from Austin, Texas, and he and John talk about their favorite ways to keep their Macs running smooth, and how to tell when it&#8217;s not! John also wraps up his Apple tech support experience for us all, as well.</p>
